From then on, the Valley of Fading Shadows learned: *a truth spoken is the foundation of the heart*. Fear may darken the lantern, but honesty, once embraced, burns brighter than the sun. And so, the valley wove a durable pattern—*stand with truth, or the Lantern will go out.* The light gleamed eternal, its trust unshaken by the weight of the world.

